    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Settlements that are located entirely or mostly in caves, usually having had development beginning with natural caves, which may have then been enlarged by excavation. For single dwellings or a relatively small number of structures in caves, use "cave architecture" or "rock-cut architecture."</Note_Text>
